snippet.textDisplay: when i played sword, i had a lot of fun, but when i played shield, i was left asking questions about the plot. for example, what exactly was the darkest day? why do some people (ie sonia) believe that there is only 1 hero when there is so much public artwork depicting there being 2 heroes? what is the calamity that rose is trying to prevent, and how would bringing about the darkest day prevent it? what's the deal with eternatus? what exactly is the relationship between leon and rose, since one tries bring the darkest day, and the other is trying to stop it, but the two of them keep acting all....buddy-like.....like they are not getting in each other's way, so are they both good guys? are they both bad guys? whats the deal with swordward and shieldbert? is each one a descendent of the 2 heroes? is there a fake one hero that wanted to revise the history and both of them are his descendents? why did they do such a terrible job hiding the true history since there is so much public art depicting 2 heroes? how does sonya not know that there are 2 heroes give the availability of this information? what's the deal with gigantimax, what is the relationship between it and zamazenta and zacian and eternatus? don't get me wrong, the game is still fun but going through the story a second time makes me realize so many unanswered plot holes that i really hope armor and crown can clear up
